              </span> <span style="text-transform: uppercase">June 29, 2026</span><br/></td></tr></tbody><tbody><tr><td align="center"/></tr></tbody></table></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><font size="3" style="FONT-FAMILY: MinionPC, Arial Unicode MS">
                    CALIFORNIA LEGISLATURE—
                    2025–2026 REGULAR SESSION</font></div><br clear="all"/><span id="bill_house_num"><div style="float: left; width:50%; font-weight: bold; "><span style="text-transform: uppercase; text-align:left;width:50%;"><b>
                Assembly Concurrent Resolution
              </b></span></div><div style="float:right; width:50%; text-align:right;"><span style="text-transform: uppercase;"><b>No. 216</b></span></div></span><hr/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td id="bill_authors" align="center"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Introduced by Assembly Members Mark González, Lackey, Schultz, and Wicks<br/>(Principal coauthors: Assembly Members Alanis, Ávila Farías, Boerner, Davies, Fong, Haney, Quirk-Silva, Michelle Rodriguez, Solache, Soria, Stefani, Valencia, and Zbur)<br/>(Principal coauthor: Senator Pérez)<br/><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>(Coauthors: Assembly Members Addis, Aguiar-Curry, Ahrens, Alvarez, Arambula, Bauer-Kahan, Bennett, Berman, Bonta, Bryan, Calderon, Caloza, Carrillo, Castillo, Chen, Connolly, DeMaio, Dixon, Elhawary, Ellis, Flora, Gabriel, Garcia, Gipson, Jeff Gonzalez, Hadwick, Harabedian, Hart, Hoover, Irwin, Kalra, Lee, Lowenthal, Macedo, McKinnor, Nguyen, Ortega, Pacheco, Papan, Patel, Patterson, Pellerin, Petrie-Norris, Ramos, Ransom, Rivas, Celeste Rodriguez, Rogers, Blanca Rubio, Sanchez, Schiavo, Sharp-Collins, Ta, Tangipa, Wallis, and Wilson)<br/></i></font></span></td></tr><tr><td id="bill_intro_date" align="center" class="textcenter"><br/>June 03, 2026</td></tr></tbody></table></div><hr/><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> Relative to Electronic Dance Music Month. </span></div><br clear="all"/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">ACR 216, as introduced, Mark González.
                          Electronic Dance Music Month.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This measure would declare the month of June 2026 as Electronic Dance Music Month.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><span class="Resolution" title="source: /caml:MeasureDoc/caml:Resolution&#xA;    "><span class="Whereas" id="id_18303816-C37E-42E0-9142-7FCF8C10B253"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Electronic dance music, or “EDM,” traces its roots back to the 1970s with the rise of disco and the innovative use of synthesizers in popular music; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_56D5182D-3644-4EA3-AAED-B39A37B0A94A"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, EDM encompasses a wide array of subgenres, including, but not limited to, disco, synthpop, techno, house, trance, drum and bass, dubstep, trap, hardstyle, and many more; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_3FE9D95C-4BB0-44F8-868D-1A1E71BAD9BB"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, EDM is a vibrant and inclusive musical form that brings people of all backgrounds together on the dance floor; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_DF2ECD59-59A5-47E4-94C7-282DBDDA2BDB"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, EDM concerts are dynamic gatherings where the music, lights, and community come together in celebration; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_E686C4AF-32C7-4246-9011-BC5824A59D7D"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Attendees of these events are the heart of the EDM movement, and are known for their passion, creativity, and expressive fashion; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_7C24D393-E8BC-4BF0-A218-393C749265D2"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, EDM culture is rooted in the core values of Peace, Love, Unity, and Respect, commonly abbreviated as “PLUR”; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_84616F73-6E8F-4924-87FD-E5B5B3082EEB"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Peace represents the elimination of conflict and the embrace of harmony; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_6922FF60-4347-4D1B-9EA0-A4C2928C2781"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Love is shared through acts of kindness and goodwill; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_8CFC33F6-36A1-46B3-B9B0-F90B639E5129"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Unity invites all people into the community regardless of background, identity, or differences; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_FF397BC8-0792-4B71-B3D8-7C9D9D7D119D"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Respect is shown through empathy, acceptance, and treating others as one wishes to be treated; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_2A888218-7C9D-4B85-BE89-8306FC366848"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, These values reflect the spirit of California, a state that celebrates diversity, inclusion, and creative expression; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_8F1E9B35-35BF-4A57-81E5-7CA7ACC25457"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, California is home to some of the world’s most iconic EDM festivals, hosted in cities across the state, including the Cities of Los Angeles, San Francisco, San Diego, San Jose, San Bernardino, Bakersfield, Palm Springs, Coachella, and across the North Coast region; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_CA8C5063-FAF9-4C6B-B0E6-A609D50B5103"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, These festivals not only serve as cultural landmarks, but also generate millions of dollars in economic impact for local communities and the state; now, therefore, be it</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_19D7C123-3F58-404E-807F-91D72C4EFC78"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved by the Assembly of the State of California, the Senate thereof concurring, That the Legislature hereby recognizes the profound cultural, social, and economic impact of EDM on the lives of Californians; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_03F3B084-2363-46F6-8A2A-AF467CA0280B"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Legislature hereby declares the month of June 2026 as Electronic Dance Music Month; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_0862DD3E-604D-413F-B3A0-565D2B162804"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Chief Clerk of the Assembly transmit copies of this resolution to the author for appropriate distribution.</div></span><div align="center"><span class="CorrectionsSeparator">___________________</span></div><br/><br/><span class="CorrectionsHeading"><span class="Correction">
